How to compile:
gcc infoli.c main.c -o infoli -O3 -lm
[-DOUTPUT_RESULTS] to print detailed information to a file named InferiorOlive_Output.txt
[-DSTEP_CHECKPOINT] to print an info message after each simulation step is done.
[-DMAX_NETWORK_SIZE=<number>] to indicate max amount of neurons in the network (default is 10000)
[-DMAX_SIMULATION_STEPS=<number>] to indicate max amount of simulation steps (default is 10000)
[-fopenmp] to run with multiple cores

How to run:
./infoli <network_size> <simulation_steps>
